<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="imlocalstd" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>imlocalstd</refname><refpurpose>Compute local intensity standard deviation.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imlocalstd(image); out = imlocalstd(image, ksize)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Input grayscale or multichannel image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>ksize</term><listitem><para>Scalar or [rows cols] box-filter size. Default is [3 3].</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imlocalstd</function> computes the square root of the local second central moment and returns double values.</para></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/coins_gray.jpg")); localStd = imlocalstd(image, [5 5]); imshow(mat2gray(localStd));]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="imlocalmean">imlocalmean</link></member><member><link linkend="imboxfilt">imboxfilt</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Function introduced in development Step 3.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
